    <div id="artwork-details">
    <div id="tombstone">

    <p>    Georgii Konstantinovich Savitskii<br />
(Born St. Petersburg, 1887; died Moscow, 1949)<br />
Dem'ian Bednyi<br />
(Born Gubovka, 1883; died Moscow, 1945)<br />
    </p>
    <h3><em>The Kolkhoz Watchman: A True Occurrence</em>, TASS No. 0531, August 18, 1942</h3>

    <p>
    Stencil<br />    2308 x 1298 mm<br />    Night. On a collective farm, <br />
Everyone asleep to get up early. <br />
Only the watchman, old man Nefed, does not sleep. <br />
Suddenly, grandfather Nefed became alarmed: <br />
Above the village rumbles a motor! <br />
Grandfather looks: It’s really a plane. <br />
Grandfather Nefed does not take his eye of it: <br />
“How marvelously the plane behaves. <br />
It’s circling right above the woods... <br />
Then it ascends fast... As if it was never there! It’s gone! <br />
What demon was it chasing down here?”<br />
Thus the old man thought, walking towards the woods:<br />
“In case I notice something.”<br />
<br />
Ah look, toward him <br />
Walks a lumbering giant.<br />
Nefed to him: “Who are you? Where from?” <br />
The giant stares; maybe lying, maybe not: <br />
“I,” he says, “have escaped captivity. <br />
I incited a German to treason. <br />
I bribed a pilot to drop me <br />
Behind Soviet lines. <br />
Where’s the road to the station? <br />
The old man feels alarmed. <br />
But his speech is moving and tricky: <br />
“Stay with us for the night. <br />
Eat, drink, and sleep. <br />
And in the morning, God bless,<br />
We'll find a horse in the collective farm<br />
To take you to the station. <br />
<br />
The nocturnal guest is in the collective farm,<br />
Everyone surrounds him…<br />
“Did you suffer in captivity?” “O, dear one, <br />
Tell us we are interested.” <br />
And the old man whispers to the cook: <br />
He is definitely lying. <br />
He says he suffered, yet his belly is huge. <br />
Matrena, run to the regional center. <br />
Tell them what’s up: During the night <br />
A crow showed up.<br />
I don't like this guest. <br />
He is evasive and he has the face of a spy.<br />
<br />
Everything became clear in the morn. <br />
The detachment from the regional center <br />
Unmasked the enemy in an instant. <br />
A German agent sneaked in here. <br />
The only legacy left of him<br />
Are his false identification, <br />
Weapons, explosive materials<br />
And a fat packet of money. <br />
He received according to the law<br />
That applies to spies: <br />
As they say: He was here, and now he's not!<br />
<br />
Having prevented harm <br />
The watchman, old man Nefed,<br />
Is now more attentive than ever <br />
On his night watch. <br />
Everyone tells him: “Thanks!”<br />
“No problem,” he laughs in response. <br />
If anyone else tries to interfere<br />
We will send him after the first <br />
To the devil for dinner!<br />    Ne boltai! Collection, Obj: 205691</p>
        
        <!--<p id="dept-gallery">--><!--<br />-->
         <!--</p>-->
    </p>
    </div><!--/tombstone-->

